# Authentication & Authorization Rules

## Route Interceptors
Use proper route interceptors based on requirements:

### Full Authentication + Authorization
```kotlin
// Requires authentication AND authorization check
momRoute("/api/endpoint", momService) { /* 8+ sessions required */ }
doctorRoute("/api/endpoint", doctorService) { /* admin authorization required */ }
adminRoute("/api/endpoint", adminService) { /* admin role required */ }
```

### Basic Authentication Only
```kotlin
// Requires authentication but NO authorization check
momRouteBasic(momService) {
    route("/api/endpoint") { /* any authenticated mom */ }
}
doctorRouteBasic(doctorService) {
    route("/api/endpoint") { /* any authenticated doctor */ }
}
```

## Key Files
- [AuthInterceptor.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/auth/AuthInterceptor.kt) - Contains all route interceptors
- [MomRoutes.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/routes/mom/MomRoutes.kt) - Mom-specific routes
- [DoctorRoutes.kt](mdc:src/main/kotlin/routes/doctor/DoctorRoutes.kt) - Doctor-specific routes

## Authorization Logic
- **Moms**: Need 8+ sessions for e-commerce access (`momRoute`)
- **Doctors**: Need admin authorization for full access (`doctorRoute`)
- **Admins**: Full system access (`adminRoute`)
- **Check Authorization**: Use `momRouteBasic`/`doctorRouteBasic` for status endpoints

## JWT Security
- Always validate JWT tokens on protected routes
- Use `call.getCurrentUserIdSafe()` to get authenticated user ID
- Implement proper token expiration and refresh mechanisms